# Project stack

Personal site + weather app: **Next.js 16**, **React 19**, **TypeScript**, **pnpm**.

## Commands

- `pnpm dev` — dev server (Next compiles SCSS on import)
- `pnpm build` — runs `build-sass` then `next build`
- `pnpm run build-sass` — optional; mirrors SCSS to `public/css/` (not used by the app)
- `pnpm lint` — ESLint

## Workflow

- Use **pnpm**, not npm or yarn.
- Keep diffs minimal; match existing patterns in the file you are editing.
- Do not commit `.env*.local` or secrets.
- **Styles:** edit `src/components/**/*.module.scss` only. Next.js compiles SCSS on import; `build-sass.mjs` mirrors to `public/css/` at build time.
- **Git:** never commit `public/css/` (gitignored). Commit `.scss` source files only.

## Path alias

Import from `@/` → `src/` (e.g. `@/components/placeInput/PlaceInput`).
